{"id": "duc04-testb-42:0#1", "contents": "While mega-mergers like the potential Exxon-Mobil deal may grab headlines, investors seeking to capitalize on the trend may find more opportunities among smaller companies. These firms' depressed stock prices are attracting bigger acquirers, whose stocks are near their peaks. According to Tom Burnett, director of Merger Insight, more deals are likely in the energy sector, which is struggling with low crude-oil prices. The healthcare industry is also expected to see increased merger activity, as executives face challenges in boosting earnings."}
